**HTML:**
<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/index.html" mode="EXCERPT">
```html
<button aria-controls="primary-nav" aria-expanded="false">
```
</augment_code_snippet>

**JavaScript:**
<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/script.js" mode="EXCERPT">
```javascript
const hamburgerButton = document.querySelector(
 '[aria-controls="primary-navigation"]'
);
```
</augment_code_snippet>

The button has `aria-controls="primary-nav"` but your JavaScript is looking for `aria-controls="primary-navigation"`.

**Fix the JavaScript:**

<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/script.js" mode="EDIT">
```javascript
const hamburgerButton = document.querySelector(
 '[aria-controls="primary-nav"]'
);
```
</augment_code_snippet>

Also, your CSS selector for the navigation doesn't match the HTML ID. Update the CSS:

<augment_code_snippet path="01-CSS-Wizard-Foundation/building-website-from-scratch/style.css" mode="EDIT">
```css
@media (width < 760px) {
 [aria-expanded="true"] + .primary-navigation {
 display: block;
 }
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

The CSS is correctly targeting `.primary-navigation` class, which matches your HTML, so that part should work once the JavaScript selector is fixed.
